CITY OF SYRACUSE v. SKANEATELES PAPER CO. et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, Fourth Department. May 4, 1895.) Appeal from special term, Onondaga county. Proceeding by the city of Syracuse against the Skaneateles Paper Company and the Lakeside Paper Company to condemn real estate. From an order denying a motion to amend the notice of appeal from final order of confirmation nunc pro tunc as of July 9, 1894, defendants appeal; and from other parts of the order, amending the notice of appeal from the final order of confirmation, plaintiff appeals. Reversed.

Argued before HARDIN, P. J., and MARTIN and MERWIN, JJ.

Knapp, Nottingham & Andrews, for appellant. C. L. Stone, W. A. Beach, and Geo. N. Kennedy, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The result reached in City of Syracuse v. Stacey, 33 N. Y. Supp. 929, as evidenced by our opinion and decision in that case, seems to supersede the necessity of considering and deciding the questions presented by the order involved in this appeal. Order vacated and set aside, without costs to either party.
